		<title>13BERNEY ARMS RAILWAY HALT</title>
		<content>   Berney Arms Halt must be almost     
 unique.Its platform is no more than 10
 metres long and possess no shelter or 
 facility of any kind.Passengers must  
 request trains to stop and as a       
 consequence a friendly rapport often  
 develops between travellers and staff 
 which would be a refreshing revelation
 to many weary city commuters.No doubt 
 this quaint anachronism will soon be  
 gone,but if it is closed it would     
 provide an ideal opportunity for one  
 of the private railway societies.     
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
